cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.MA 

This paper deals with the problem of decentralized optimization and learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of kernel learning and random feature approximation suggests that the paper may fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on communication efficiency and privacy preservation suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of distributed consensus algorithms and communication-censoring strategies suggests that it may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
